  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "During training, a weakly supervised tumor detection system only has access to a label on a slide level.",
    "For example, the label could denote: \"does this slide contain a tumor, yes or no?\".",
    "An alternative approach is \"strongly\" supervised learning.",
    "Here, the objective is to delineate tumor tissue or detect cell types based on accurate, manual annotations.",
    "Weakly supervised approaches obviate the need for manual annotation and, hence, are more scalable to large image archives."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}